Defendant in custody.   
Count 1 - PTC Fraud Against Financial Institution - No contest plea.   
Count 2 - PTC Fraud Against Financial Institution - No contest plea.   Convicted.   State moves to dismiss and read in count 3, PTC Fraud Against Financial Institution.   Motion granted.   
Sentences are withheld.   Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for two (2) years, to commence upon defendant's discharge date after extended supervision in Case Files 15 CF 451 and 15 CF 629.    Conditions of probation are:
1) AODA assessment and follow through; 
2) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
3) Maintain full-time employment/schooling combination; 
4) Have no contact with Community First Credit Union; 
5) Pay restitution of $1,461.00 to Community First Credit Union, joint and several with Christopher Bryan;
6) Pay costs of action; 
7) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC; 
8) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
9) Maintain absolute sobriety.   
